  "text": "Due to limitations in practical applications, existing contact or non-contact deflection transducers rarely meet the need for the deflection measurement in the SHM of long span bridges. Combining the distributed long gauge sensing technique and classical conjugate beam method, this paper recommends a solution to measure the displacement and the rotational angle [CITATION_1] . The basic idea is to transfer the deformation in the real beam into the internal forces in the virtual beam whose shear force and bending moment are equal to the rotational angle and the displacement of the real beam respectively. ",
